        <div class="step-box">
            <div class="step-header">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <h2 class="step-title">Create Shop Account</h2>
            </div>
            
            <p><strong>First step:</strong> Register your Etsy seller account to get started. Visit <strong>Etsy.com → "Sell on Etsy" → Register</strong> to begin your journey.</p>
            
            <div class="alert alert-warning">
                <strong>⚠️ Important Requirements:</strong> You'll need government-issued ID and tax information ready for verification. This process typically takes 5-10 minutes but ensures your account security and buyer trust.
            </div>

            <div class="pro-tip">
                <div class="pro-tip-header"onclick="toggleProTip(this)">
                    📸 Pro Tip: Account Setup Best Practices
                    <span class="pro-tip-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="pro-tip-content">
                    <h4>Essential Account Setup Steps:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Professional Email:</strong> Use a business email address (yourname@yourdomain.com) rather than personal Gmail for credibility</li>
                        <li><strong>Strong Password:</strong> 12+ characters with uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols - use a password manager</li>
                        <li><strong>Profile Photo:</strong> Use a clear headshot or professional logo in square format (400x400px minimum)</li>
                        <li><strong>Two-Factor Authentication:</strong> Enable immediately for account security - this is crucial for business accounts</li>
                        <li><strong>Phone Verification:</strong> Add your phone number for account recovery and buyer trust signals</li>
                        <li><strong>Complete Profile:</strong> Fill out all sections including bio, location, and social media links</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>Time-Saving Preparation Tips:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have your business information, tax ID (EIN), and banking details ready before starting</li>
                        <li>Prepare a 2-3 sentence bio about your creative journey and what makes your products special</li>
                        <li>Take a high-quality profile photo in advance with good lighting and professional appearance</li>
                        <li>Research your competitors' profiles to see what works in your niche</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

