            </div>
            
            <p><strong>Choose wisely:</strong> Your shop name is permanent and becomes your brand identity. It must be 4-20 characters and effectively represent your products and personality.</p>

            <div class="interactive-form">
                <h4>🎯 Shop Name Brainstorming Tool</h4>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label class="form-label" for="shopNameInput">Test Your Shop Name Ideas:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="shopNameInput" class="form-input" placeholder="e.g., CozyWoodCrafts, VintageGemFinds, ArtisanAlley, CreativeCorner" oninput="validateShopName()">
                    <small id="nameValidation" style="display: block; margin-top: 8px; font-weight: 500;"></small>
                </div>
                
                <button class="btn" onclick="generateRandomName()">🎲 Generate Random Name</button>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                    <strong>💡 Popular Name Patterns:</strong><br>
                    <strong>Descriptive:</strong> CozyWoodCrafts • VintageGemFinds • RusticHomeDecor<br>
                    <strong>Personal:</strong> SarahsStudio • EmmaMakes • AlexArtistry<br>
                    <strong>Creative:</strong> MoonbeamMakers • StardustStudio • DreamCrafters<br>
                    <strong>Modern:</strong> ZenCraft • PureMakers • EchoDesigns
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pro-tip">
                <div class="pro-tip-header"onclick="toggleProTip(this)">
                    💡 Pro Tip: Shop Naming Strategy That Converts
                    <span class="pro-tip-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="pro-tip-content">
                    <h4>The Perfect Shop Name Formula:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Include Product Keywords:</strong> Wood, Vintage, Handmade, Art, Craft, Studio - helps with Etsy search</li>
                        <li><strong>Keep It Memorable:</strong> 4-15 characters work best for word-of-mouth marketing and easy typing</li>
                        <li><strong>Easy to Spell:</strong> Avoid complex words, numbers, or unusual spellings that confuse customers</li>
                        <li><strong>Think Long-term:</strong> Don't limit yourself to just one product category - allow room for growth</li>
                        <li><strong>Check Social Media:</strong> Ensure the name is available across Instagram, Pinterest, Facebook, TikTok</li>
                        <li><strong>Test Pronunciation:</strong> Say it out loud - customers should be able to remember and recommend you</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>Proven Examples by Category:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Jewelry & Accessories:</strong> GemGlow, SilverStream, BaubleBox, CharmCraft, SparkleStudio</li>
                        <li><strong>Home & Living:</strong> CozyNook, RusticRoots, ModernNest, HomeHaven, ComfortCrafts</li>
                        <li><strong>Art & Prints:</strong> ColorCraft, ArtisanAlley, CreativeCorner, StudioSpark, InkAndImagination</li>
                        <li><strong>Vintage & Antiques:</strong> TimeTreasures, RetroRevival, VintageVault, PastPerfect, EraElegance</li>
                        <li><strong>Handmade Crafts:</strong> MakersMoon, CraftedCharm, HandmadeHeart, StitchStudio, CreatedWithLove</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>Name Testing Checklist:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Search Etsy to ensure it's not already taken or too similar to existing shops</li>
                        <li>Check domain availability (yourshoponame.com) for future website expansion</li>
                        <li>Ask friends if they can spell it correctly after hearing it once</li>
                        <li>Imagine it on business cards, packaging, and social media - does it look professional?</li>
                        <li>Consider trademark issues - avoid using brand names or copyrighted terms</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

