            <div class="pro-tip">
                <div class="pro-tip-header"onclick="toggleProTip(this)">
                    🎯 Pro Tip: Launch Week Strategy That Works
                    <span class="pro-tip-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="pro-tip-content">
                    <h4>Week Before Launch:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Monday-Tuesday:</strong> Final product photos, complete all listings, test checkout process</li>
                        <li><strong>Wednesday-Thursday:</strong> Write launch announcement content, prepare social media posts</li>
                        <li><strong>Friday-Weekend:</strong> Soft launch to family/friends for feedback and first reviews</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>Launch Week (Recommended: Tuesday-Thursday):</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Day 1:</strong> Official announcement on personal social media, email to contacts</li>
                        <li><strong>Day 2-3:</strong> Join Etsy seller Facebook groups, share in relevant communities</li>
                        <li><strong>Day 4-5:</strong> Start Pinterest marketing, create boards for your products</li>
                        <li><strong>Weekend:</strong> Engage with customers, respond to messages, analyze first week data</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>First Month Marketing Strategy:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Etsy Ads:</strong> Start with $5-10/day budget, focus on your best listings</li>
                        <li><strong>SEO Optimization:</strong> Update titles and tags based on search performance</li>
                        <li><strong>Social Proof:</strong> Encourage reviews, share customer photos (with permission)</li>
                        <li><strong>Content Marketing:</strong> Behind-the-scenes posts, process videos, customer stories</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>Success Metrics to Track:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Week 1 Goal:</strong> 10+ shop favorites, 3+ listing favorites per item</li>
                        <li><strong>Month 1 Goal:</strong> First 5 sales (even if from friends/family)</li>
                        <li><strong>Month 2 Goal:</strong> 10+ sales, 5-star average rating, repeat customers</li>
                        <li><strong>Month 3 Goal:</strong> Consistent weekly sales, established brand presence</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

